plpa|-----handy-ruler------------------------------------------------------|
plpa: plpa (ortable Linux Processor Affinity)
plpa:
plpa: PLPA is an attempt to solve the problem that there are multiple API's
plpa: for processor affinity within Linux. Specifically, the functions
plpa: sched_setaffinity() and sched_getaffinity() have numbers and types of
plpa: parameters depending on your Linux vendor and/or version of GLibc.
plpa: This is quite problematic for applications attempting to use processor
plpa: affinity in Linux for compile-time, link-time, and run-time reasons.
plpa:
plpa: http://www.open-mpi.org/projects/plpa/
plpa: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
